#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:6
msgid "Math Module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:8
msgid ""
"The ``math`` module is a standard library module that provides mathematical "
"functions. Import it with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:10
msgid "import math"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:14
msgid "Functions are then called as ``math.isqrt(x)``, ``math.sqrt(d)``, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:18
msgid ""
"``import math`` always refers to the standard library module. To import a "
"local file named ``math.vy``, use a relative import: ``from . import math``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:21
msgid "Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:25
msgid ""
"Return the square root of the provided decimal number, using the Babylonian "
"square root algorithm. The rounding mode is to round down to the nearest "
"epsilon. For instance, ``math.sqrt(0.9999999998) == 0.9999999998``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:27
msgid ""
"import math\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"@view\n"
"def foo(d: decimal) -> decimal:\n"
"    return math.sqrt(d)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:36
msgid ""
">>> ExampleContract.foo(9.0)\n"
"3.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:43
msgid ""
"Return the (integer) square root of the provided integer number, using the "
"Babylonian square root algorithm. The rounding mode is to round down to the "
"nearest integer. For instance, ``math.isqrt(101) == 10``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:45
msgid ""
"import math\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"@view\n"
"def foo(x: uint256) -> uint256:\n"
"    return math.isqrt(x)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../stdlib-math.rst:54
msgid ""
">>> ExampleContract.foo(101)\n"
"10"
msgstr ""

